    "title": "Guided Practice: Identifying TN-S Systems",
    "objective": "Identify a TN-S earthing system and the conductor connecting the MET to the means of earthing.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Step 1: Observe the supply intake. If the earth path is provided by a separate conductor (like a lead sheath) back to the transformer, it is a TN-S system.",
      "Step 2: Identify the conductor that links the Main Earthing Terminal (MET) to that supplier earth terminal. This is the Earthing Conductor.",
      "Step 3: Remember that the CPC only runs from the MET to the individual circuits, not to the supply earth."
    ],
    "questionText": "You are at an older property where the earth is provided by a metal clamp on the lead sheath of the supplier's incoming cable. A green and yellow cable runs from this clamp to the MET. Identify the earthing system type and the specific name of the conductor connecting the clamp to the MET.",
    "answerGuidance": [
